        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whisk together the plain flour, rice flour, desiccated coconut, sugar, baking powder, and salt. Add the cold water and whisk to a smooth, slightly thick batter. Rest for 15 minutes. Heat the oil to 180°C in a deep saucepan.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Dip each banana half into the batter, coating thoroughly, and let the excess drip off. Lower carefully into the oil and fry in batches of 3 to 4 pieces for 2 minutes per side until golden. Remove with a slotted spoon and drain briefly on paper before transferring to a rack. Dust with icing sugar and serve immediately.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
